Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Sub-Unit  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 11 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected a sub-unit of KPA navy unit 291. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After learning about the sub-unit's performance of duty, he went round combat and technical equipment. He expressed satisfaction over the fact that its servicepersons are prizing and handling with care combat and technical equipment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round the cozy barracks and their compound, he praised the sub-unit for keeping its post in good order after sprucing up it well. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He made the rounds of an educational room, bedroom, a mess hall, a wash-cum-bath house and a daily provision store and other entertainment and educational and supply service facilities. No details escaped his attention ranging from beds of seamen to the processing of non-staple food and its storage and their tastes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He appreciated the efforts made by the commanding officers of the unit, pleased to learn that they have provided their soldiers with good living conditions, bearing deep in mind the teaching of President Kim Il Sung that the supply service precisely means a political work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Informed of the preparations for wintering by commanding officers of the sub-unit, he told them to make thoroughgoing measures for wintering so that the soldiers may spend the winter under warm conditions as cold weather is expected to come before long. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underscoring the need to pay particular attention to the living of seamen as they are active in rough seas in all seasons, he said all the commanding officers should have warm love for the soldiers and take paternal care of them so that they might not feel even the slightest inconvenience in their living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave the servicepersons of the sub-unit a pair of binoculars and an automatic rifle as gifts before having a photo session with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Myong Su and Senior Vice Admiral Choe Pu Il and Ri Yong Chol, first vice department director of the C.C., the WPK.

KCNA Urges Japan to Make Political Decision  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 10 (KCNA) -- The international community has expected a change in Japan's foreign policy since the appearance of a new Cabinet and new prime minister there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But nothing has changed in its foreign policy orientation including its policy towards the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At a recent meeting of the working group on economic and energy aid of the six-party talks Japan sidestepped economic aid to the DPRK under the pretext of the "abduction issue." It is persisting in its unilateral sanctions against the DPRK. The House of Representatives of Japan approved another bill on extending the sanctions against the DPRK including a total ban on imports from the DPRK and embargo on DPRK-flagged ships. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This proves that it has not departed even a bit from the mean political mode whereby its preceding regime adopted it as a policy to slap sanctions on the DPRK, oft-repeating a trite stance that it can never take part in economic aid unless progress is made in settling the "abduction issue." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As well known, the DPRK has taken practical measures for the denuclearization under an agreement adopted by the six parties and the countries concerned have sincerely honored their commitments under it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, it is only Japan which is throwing a hurdle in the way of the talks while evading the commitment it made at the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said facts raise a question as to whether Japan is qualified to attend the six-party talks or not. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the calculation of the Japanese ultra-nationalists that they can secure a justification for militarization and nuclear weaponization by scuttling the six-party talks aimed at settling the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present Japanese Cabinet seems to be not in a position to make any decision to make a switchover in its foreign policy as it is under the strong pressure of ultra-right conservative forces at home. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's sanctions against the DPRK are quite contrary to the trend of the overall international situation and will only result in making the hostile relations between the DPRK and Japan further fester. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It would be a right option for Japan to drop its trite, hard-line and conservative approach toward the DPRK and thus swim with the trend of the times.

MOU Signed between Pyongyang and Jakarta 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 10 (KCNA) -- A memorandum of understanding on establishing the sister city relations between Pyongyang of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and Jakarta of the Republic of Indonesia was signed in Jakarta on Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The MOU was inked by Vice-Chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee Kim Jong Sik and the mayor of Jakarta.

Greetings to Angolan President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 10 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Jose Eduardo Dos Santos, President of Angola, on Nov. 8 on the occasion of the 32nd anniversary of its independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the message Kim Yong Nam wished the Angolan president greater success in his responsible work for national unity and economic development of Angola, expressing the belief that the long-standing friendly ties and excellent relations of cooperation between the peoples of the two countries would grow stronger in different fields.

Message of Sympathy to Dominican President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 10 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Friday sent a message of sympathy to Leonel Fernandez Reyna, President of the Dominican Republic, in connection with the tropical storm Noel that hit the Caribbean region recently, claiming many casualties and material losses in the republic. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim in the message expressed deep sympathy and consolation to the Dominican president and, through him, to the government and the people in the afflicted area and hoped that the government would eradicate the aftermath of the natural disaster and bring their living to normal as early as possible.

Korean Revolution Museum, House of Revolutionary Treasures 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 10 (KCNA) -- The Korean Revolution Museum is a house of revolutionary treasures and an important centre of education in the revolutionary traditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has more than 90 exhibition rooms according to the periods and sectors of the revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary relics and data associated with the activities of the three generals of Mt. Paektu in the years including the period of the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle, the period of the anti-imperialist, anti-feudal democratic revolution and the first period of the transition to socialism after the liberation of the country, the period of the Fatherland Liberation War, the periods of the socialist revolution and the building of the foundations of socialism and the period of completing the socialist industrialization are displayed at the museum in a systematic way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The museum was supplemented in April 1995 with six rooms showing in depth the immortal exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung in the efforts for the complete victory of socialism (1980s-1990s) and for the country's reunification (1980s-1990s). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The hall of the leader and comrades-in-arms was opened to the public on April 12, 1999 to show the lofty world of love and fidelity between the leader and the soldiers. Some 20 pieces of revolutionary materials of anti-Japanese woman hero Kim Jong Suk in the period of building a new country were also on display in supplement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nearly 800 pieces of historical materials including photographs and revolutionary data of Kim Jong Il who is wisely leading the efforts for building the great prosperous and powerful nation are also exhibited in three rooms of the museum. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recently the museum has developed and used the computer multimedia and integrated management system of revolutionary data "Eternal Treasure" which show the revolutionary relics and data associated with the revolutionary activities of the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The museum was founded on August 1, Juche 37 (1948).

DPRK's Stand to Boost South-South Cooperation Reiterated 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 11 (KCNA) -- The DPRK will as ever perform its responsibility and role in the efforts to establish a new international economic order based on justice, equality and impartiality and boost South-South cooperation based on collective self-reliance and thus make a positive contribution to building a new world, independent and equal, says Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present situation calls for foiling the imperialists' unjust moves and boosting the South-South cooperation in all fields, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The development of the South-South cooperation will make it possible for developing countries to get rid of economic subordination and dependence on the West and successfully build self-supporting national economy. If the South-South cooperation is developed in all fields, it will be quite easy to neutralize the present unequal international economic system and build a new fair international economic order. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people in the developing countries which won their independence have worked hard for social progress and national prosperity with common desire to realize independence. The commonness in past life, present desire and purpose of struggle provides a groundwork for the people in those countries to unite and boost the South-South cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The developing countries have enough conditions and possibilities for the South-South cooperation. If they boost economic cooperation and exchange useful technologies and experience with each other by making good use of their own economic potentials and possibilities, they can surely build self-supporting national economy and ensure their prosperous development and national prosperity without relaying on the West. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the consistent stand of the DPRK to boost the South-South cooperation. Over the past years the DPRK government has paid deep attention to strengthening the cooperation and rendered disinterested support and exerted much effort while taking an active part in the activities of the Non-aligned Movement, G-77 and UN organizations. In this course, it has accumulated a wealth of experience and made signal achievements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK, as it committed at the Second South Summit, proposed cooperation projects in different fields for developing countries in Asia and Africa and has exerted efforts for their implementation this year as it did last year.

Koreans Called upon to Achieve Great National Unity 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 10 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il's idea and policy of great national unity serve as immortal guidelines for achieving national unity and the cause of national reunification as they call for achieving the great unity of the entire nation on the basis of the principle of national independence and under the banner of patriotism, the banner of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Saturday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The principle of national independence represents a core issue in solving the national problem and a foundation for achieving the great unity of the whole nation, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koreans raise the issue of the great unity of the nation as the most urgent demand at present in order to establish national sovereignty throughout Korea and accomplish the cause of national reunification and achieve prosperity common to the nation by its concerted efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 National independence guarantees the destiny and prosperity of the nation. It is senseless to talk about the great unity and reunification of the nation away from the principle of national independence because the great unity of the nation based on the above-said principle alone can always remain vital and fully display its might. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans' spirit of patriotism and national disposition peculiar to them serve as an ideological and moral mainstay for the great unity of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their unanimous desire and will for reunification are a clear manifestation of their strong national self-esteem and patriotic traits to put an end to the history of the tragedy of national division as early as possible and build a reunified and prosperous country on this land and thus greatly exalt the dignity and honor of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This patriotic spirit and national disposition common to the Koreans should be regarded as an ideological and moral mainstay for achieving the great unity of the nation. Only by doing so, can they achieve the great unity of the entire nation irrespective of ideology, ism, political view and religious belief and differing interests of classes and strata that exist among them.

Abolition of NSL Demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 11 (KCNA) -- The People's Solidarity for the Abolition of the "National Security Law" in south Korea reportedly issued a statement titled "Immediately set free detainees and abolish the NSL" on Nov. 6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement recalled that on Tuesday the security authorities walked off Ra Jin Suk, chairperson of the General Student Council of Konkuk University for 2002, and Hong Ki Ung, vice-chairman of the General Student Council of Seoul Industrial University for 2003, who participated in the struggle for the abolition of the NSL staged in Seoul. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At present many students affiliated with the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) have been detained and sought on the want list so that they cannot enjoy even elementary human rights, it said, deploring the attitude of the security authorities cracking down on the progressive student organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an undemocratic act to brand Hanchongryon as an "enemy-befitting organization", going against the trend of the times today when reconciliation, cooperation and exchange are getting brisk between the south and the north, the statement said, urging the south Korean authorities to immediately release those detained and repeal the NSL.

Massive Practical Action for Abolition of NSL Declared in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 10 (KCNA) -- The People's Solidarity for the Abolition of the "National Security Law (NSL)" of south Korea reportedly called a press conference in Seoul on Nov. 5 at which it declared that it would launch a massive practical action for the abolition of the evil law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the press conference deplored that the NSL is denounced by all circles as an evil law in the era but the authorities are lending a deaf ear to this. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They demanded the "National Assembly" immediately pass the "bill on abolishing the NSL" as agreed by the south and the north to adjust the legal and institutional mechanisms with a view to developing the south-north relations to meet the purpose of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed that the progressive organizations of all circles would wage a sustained massive practical action for the abolition of the NSL. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the press conference members of the organization marched as far as the building of the "National Assembly".

S. Korean Police Authorities Walk Off Former Deputies to Hanchongryon
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 10 (KCNA) -- The south Korean police authorities reportedly walked off Ra Jin Suk, chairperson of the General Student Council of Konkuk University for 2002, and Hong Ki Ung, vice-chairman of the General Student Council of Seoul Industrial University for 2003, who are former deputies to the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) on Nov. 6. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ra and Hong attended a demonstration staged by organizations of all circles in demand of the abolition of the "National Security Law" on the same day.  The police arrested them on the scene of action after keeping them on the want list for several years for the mere reason that they were active as deputies to Hanchongryon.

Kim Il Sung's Work Studied in Nigeria
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 11 (KCNA) -- A meeting for explaining "3. Let Us Reunify the Country Independently and Peacefully" of "Report to the Sixth Congress of the Workers' Party of Korea on the Work of the Central Committee," a work of President Kim Il Sung, was held by the Nigerian Group for the Study of the Songun Politics on Oct. 25 to mark the 27th anniversary of the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting an explanation of the work was given before speeches were made by M. M. Alhassan, chairman of the Nigerian National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea, and the chairman of the above-mentioned group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said that President Kim Il Sung embarked on the road of revolution in his early years, liberated the country through armed struggle and built a powerful socialist state, independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defence, in Korea by successfully carrying out the revolution of several stages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Stressing that the President had worked heart and soul to reunify the country divided by foreign forces, the speakers noted that he examined a document related to the matter of national reunification even in the last moments of his life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il opened up a bright vista for Korea's reunification, they said, expressing belief that the Korean people would certainly achieve national reunification by smashing every obstructive maneuver of the outsiders.

Korean People's Cause Supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, November 11 (KCNA) -- A resolution supporting the revolutionary cause of the Workers' Party of Korea and the Korean people was unanimously adopted on Monday at the international meeting of communist and workers' parties held in Minsk, Belarus, to mark the 90th anniversary of the October Socialist Revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolution reads: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Today the Korean people are pushing ahead with the general advance of the Songun revolution to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation under the leadership of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The WPK and the Korean people's revolutionary cause of Songun is the sacred cause for defending the sovereignty and dignity of the country and the nation and the banner of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In recent years the Korean people have made signal achievements in the efforts to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation by increasing the national capability for self-defence and activating the national economy under the Songun leadership of the WPK and reunify the country as soon as possible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To fully support the Songun revolutionary cause of the WPK and the Korean people is a major link of the whole chain for advocating and developing the international socialist movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The communist and workers' parties of different countries participating in the international meeting of communist and workers' parties to mark the 90th anniversary of the October Socialist Revolution express full support and solidarity with the just struggle of the Korean people to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country by the nation itself, free from outsiders' interference, holding high the banner of Songun under the leadership of the WPK.

Meeting for Koreans' Human Rights Held in Japan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, November 9 (KNS-KCNA) -- The 2007 national meeting for "History of Koreans in Japan and week of human rights" was held in Yamaguchi, Japan, on Nov. 3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending there were Ko Tok U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and director of its Department for Compatriots' Living, Sumiko Shimizu, representative of the Japanese Women's Society for Solidarity with the Korean Women, and Akihiro Harata, co-representative of the Central Headquarters of the Japanese Side to the Fact-finding Group on Forcible Drafting of Koreans, who are co-representatives of the executive committee for the meeting, and other officials concerned, Korean residents in Japan and Japanese people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting dealt with the illegality of the "Ulsa Five-point Treaty" faked up by the Japanese imperialists in 1905, the issue of the remains of victims to forcible drafting, the Japanese government's hostile policy toward Japan-resident Koreans seen through the convention on abolition of racial discrimination, other matters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ko Tok U made an address at the meeting before reports were made by Hong Sang Jin, secretary general of the Central Headquarters of the Korean Side to the Fact-finding Group, Takafumi Shima, honorary professor of Yamaguchi University, and Akira Maeta, professor of Tokyo Zokei College. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporters charged that the Japanese government is still evading its historical responsibility for the tragic death of Korean victims to the forcible drafting by Japan and, on the contrary, is being hell-bent on violation of rights of Koreans in Japan, descendants of the victims, and unreasonable suppression of Chongryon organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting heard a testimony made by Kim Sung Ho, chairman of the Hyogo Prefectural Association of Korean Workers in Commerce in Japan, who is a bereaved family member of the victims of forcible drafting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An appeal was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the meeting, there was a memorial service for the victims of forcible drafting.

Kim Jong Il inspecciona comandancia de la Unidad No. 627 del EPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 10 de noviembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea (PTC), Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea (EPC), inspecciono la comandancia de la Unidad No. 627 del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Despues de recorrer la sala de presentacion del historial de la unidad, el Dirigente entro en la sala de leccion militar, donde se entero del estado de cumplimiento del deber de guardia de la unidad y del entrenamiento de los oficiales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Expreso satisfaccion de que la unidad entrena a todos los oficiales como miembros de mando dispuestos de alta capacidad de organizacion operacional y combativa y de mando. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al recorrer la Casa de Militares y la biblioteca elogio que la unidad libra de manera activa la labor de educacion politica e ideologica utilizando con eficacia diversos datos y, en particular, al establecer el ambiente revolucionario de lectura forma a los militares como seres preparados en multiples aspectos con ricos conocimientos y preparacion cultural. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Todos los hombres deben leer asiduamente el libro que es el excelente guia de la vida y maestro, senalo y continuo que para hacer que muchos militares lean durante largo tiempo los valiosos libros es preciso conservarlos y cuidarlos bien. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En los ultimos anos el Ejercito Popular, al desplegar ampliamente la labor para suscitar el ansia de lectura de los militares, arma con mas firmeza a estos con la idea revolucionaria de nuestro partido y eleva incesantemente la preparacion cultural de estos, dijo el y enfatizo que este ambiente de lectura establecido en todo el ejercito deviene otro rasgo orgulloso que se puede ver solo en nuestro ejercito revolucionario que orienta la epoca del Songun (priorizacion militar). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al recorrer las instalaciones de intendencia de la unidad, se mostro alegre de que la unidad acondiciono bien diversas instalaciones de intendencia comodas para la vida de los militares y de que los oficiales atienden cordialmente con el amor fraternal a los soldados, y elogio los sinceros esfuerzos de los oficiales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Informado de que la gran unidad combinada a que pertenece esta unidad construye una nueva base de intendencia para preparar las excelentes condiciones de vida alimentaria de los militares, lo califico de una cosa buena, indico los medios para impulsarla con energia y dio solucion a los problemas pendientes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al decir que la unidad hizo muchos esfuerzos tambien en la labor para la proteccion territorial y medioambiental, aparte de la labor para fortalecer la capacidad combativa, elogio altamente sus exitos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente se fotografio junto a los militares de la Unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Le acompanaron los generales de ejercito del EPC Hyon Chol Hae y Ri Myong Su y el primer subjefe de departamento del CC del PTC Ri Yong Chol.

Firmada nota sobre hermanamiento entre Pyongyang y Yakarta
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 10 de noviembre (ATCC) -- Quedo rubricada el dia 8 en Yakarta la nota de entendimiento sobre el establecimiento de las relaciones de ciudades hermanas entre Pyongyang de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Yakarta de la Republica de Indonesia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La suscribieron el vicepresidente del Comite Popular de la Ciudad de Pyongyang, Kim Jong Sik, y el alcalde de Yakarta.
